    public class DriveEncoderGyroRampRel
extends DriveEncoderGyroRamp
    Drive the robot a specified distance using encoders and the gyro to keep straight and ramp up to full speed. Finish when one of the encoders is within the specified tolerance. The distance is relative to the Robot's current position. The angle is relative to the angle where the robot started. The angle should be close to the current angle of the robot (ie this command is not appropriate for both turning and driving). If the robot needs to turn prior to driving straight, use TurnGyroAbs first.

    For example, to drive 10 feet forward, set distance to 120 (inches) and set angle to 0. A reasonable tolerance is 3 inches for normal movements. This will stop the robot when it is between 117 - 123 inches. If a smaller tolerance is used, the robot may not ever reach the tolerance, and the timeout will be exceeded. This will slow down the execution of future commands.

    Joe
